dīkṣā ∈ [
	, "," 8< jñānam >8
	, "¡" 8< eager preprocessed mantra >8
	, ";" 8< lazy preprocessed mantra >8
	, "!" 8< eager postprocessed mantra >8
	, ":" 8< lazy postprocessed mantra >8
	, "∴" 8< return; could use ↵ or \r or ⏎ or ⌤ or ETC >8
	, "∵" 8< reason >8
	, "." 8< dexing >8
]

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Evaluation_strategy
different dīkṣā can be for lazy vs eager vs ETC evaluations
	!eager()
	¡eager_precomputation() 8≪ ¡nteresting()
	:lazy()
	;lazy_precomputation()
	...or...
	:lazy()
	::eager()
	;lazy_precomputation()
	;;eager_precomputation()
	...it's probably better to use different symbols to avoid typographical bugs (misunderstandings/mistakes/ETC); avoid querying if you're sure you meant one/two/ETC
